Code preview of the table States_Flag

USE DATABASECOUNTRYHL
go

IF EXISTS (SELECT 1
FROM SYS.SYSREFERENCES R JOIN SYS.SYSOBJECTS O ON (O.ID = R.CONSTID AND O.TYPE = 'F')
WHERE R.FKEYID = OBJECT_ID('STATES_FLAG') AND O.NAME = 'FK_STATES_F_STATES_FO_STATES')
ALTER TABLE STATES_FLAG
DROP CONSTRAINT FK_STATES_F_STATES_FO_STATES
go

IF EXISTS (SELECT 1
FROM SYSINDEXES
WHERE ID = OBJECT_ID('STATES_FLAG')
AND NAME = 'STATE_FOR_FLAGSTATE_FK'
AND INDID > 0
AND INDID < 255)
DROP INDEX STATES_FLAG.STATE_FOR_FLAGSTATE_FK
go

ALTER TABLE STATES_FLAG
DROP CONSTRAINT PK_STATES_FLAG
go

IF EXISTS (SELECT 1
FROM SYSOBJECTS
WHERE ID = OBJECT_ID('STATES_FLAG')
AND TYPE = 'U')
DROP TABLE STATES_FLAG
go

/*==============================================================*/
/* Table: STATES_FLAG */
/*==============================================================*/
CREATE TABLE STATES_FLAG (
STF_ID INT IDENTITY,
STA_ID INT NOT NULL,
STF_FLAG VARBINARY(8000) NOT NULL
)
go

ALTER TABLE STATES_FLAG
ADD CONSTRAINT PK_STATES_FLAG PRIMARY KEY (STF_ID)
go

/*==============================================================*/
/* Index: STATE_FOR_FLAGSTATE_FK */
/*==============================================================*/




CREATE NONCLUSTERED INDEX STATE_FOR_FLAGSTATE_FK ON STATES_FLAG (STA_ID ASC)
go

ALTER TABLE STATES_FLAG
ADD CONSTRAINT FK_STATES_F_STATES_FO_STATES FOREIGN KEY (STA_ID)
REFERENCES STATES (STA_ID)
go
